{
  "texts": [
    "The fact that the transition temperature rises for ~50 K due to the increment in the PIN (Pb(In 1/2 Nb 1/2)O 3) portion from 29% to 36% is in line with the experimental observations 90, 91.",
    "In this work, we introduce DPA-2, a newly designed model architecture for the Large Atomic Model (LAM), supported by a comprehensive pipeline that includes multi-task pre-training, fine-tuning, knowledge distillation, and practical deployment.",
    "The principal findings concerning DPA-2 are as follows: (1) DPA-2 demonstrates exceptional ability for generalization, primarily due to the multi-task pre-training approach, which utilizes 18 datasets covering 73 chemical elements.",
    "These datasets would not typically be merged in a single-task pre-training scenario due to differing labeling methodologies, such as exchange-correlation functionals, energy cutoffs, and k-space grid spacing.",
    "(2) The multi-task pretraining approach significantly enhances zero-shot generalization on downstream tasks."
  ]
}